==Translingual==
===Symbol===
'''Γ''' 
# The [[upper case]] letter [[gamma]], the third letter of the modern [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek alphabet]].

'''Γ''''
# The number three in [[w:Greek numerals|Greek numerals]].

''',Γ'''
# The number 3000 in Greek numerals.

===Etymology===
* Derived from the [[Phoenician]] letter [[w:Gimel (letter)|Gimel]] [[Image:phoenician_gimel.png|20px|Beth]].

===Pronunciation===
* In modern Greek it represents ...

